    <div id="comment_36584988">
        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Insightful">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:As an American Conservative..."><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:As an American Conservative...<span> (4, Insightful)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~JSBiff" class="author" title="author name and user ID">JSBiff (87824) </a> | about 3 years ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2274044&cid=36584988">(#36584988)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_36584988" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Insightful">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>You totally missed the point since you stopped reading. The GP isn't saying the government is requiring something of the parents, but simply that because the government is NOT requiring retailers to police what games children buy/play, by default, the parents are required (not by law, but by the LACK of law, and by their own set of standards) to take responsibility for what they do and don't want their children playing.</p><p>That is to say, the parents are required by their own conscience to BE good parents, or not.</p></div>
