            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about 3 years ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=2274044&cid=36585762">(#36585762)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_36585762" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="0" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body">The article mentions books as a comparison, so here's mine. <br>
If it's a-ok for a 5 year old to buy an M game, is it then, a-ok for that same 5 year old to go buy porn? Then waltz into a theatre and see an R rated movie?
Don't get me wrong, I agree this shouldn't be a law, but I just don't like the comparison.</div>
